# Achronyme language files
*.ach linguist-language=Achronyme
*.ach linguist-detectable

# Circom fixtures and vendored circomlib — not Achronyme's source, exclude
# from GitHub language statistics. Most of the `.circom` mass in this
# repo comes from `test/circomlib/` (the iden3/circomlib subset we
# vendor for E2E tests) plus small standalone fixtures under
# `test/circom/`. Marking the extension globally keeps tornado-style
# vendored sub-trees under `examples/` out of the stats too.
*.circom linguist-vendored
*.circom linguist-generated=false
